title: PMLN’ candidate Sardar Muhammad Yousaf Zaman wins NA-14 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan Muslim League Nawaz Candidate Sardar Muhammad Yousaf Zaman has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-14 Mansehra by securing 115,544 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Independent Candidate Muhammad Saleem Imran, who bagged 103,333 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 44.77 percent.
